quote: Look up.
author: Luanne Rice,  Silver Bells

quote: Look beyond yourself..
author: Michael Jackson

quote: Look at me!Look at me!Look at me NOW!It is fun to have funBut you have to know how.
author: Dr. Seuss,  The Cat in the Hat (Deluxe Edition)

quote: Don't look at me in that tone of voice.
author: Dorothy Parker

quote: I don't know how I look, but I know how I feel: Young. Goofy. Infinite.
author: John Green,  Paper Towns

quote: See mirror, every time you will miss me and look deeper into your eyes till you will find me.
author: Santosh Kalwar,  Quote Me Everyday

quote: When in doubt, look intelligent.
author: Garrison Keillor

quote: Can you look without the voice in your head commenting, drawing conclusions, comparing, or trying to figure something out?
author: Eckhart Tolle,  A New Earth: Awakening to Your Life's Purpose

quote: Hello! Look at me! I am your reflection.
author: Debasish Mridha

quote: It's not what you look at that matters, it's what you see.
author: Henry David Thoreau

quote: Eyes shows lies.
author: Toba Beta,  My Ancestor Was an Ancient Astronaut

quote: I don't want anyone to look to me, not for protection, not for happiness, not for love, not for anything.
author: P.D. James,  The Children of Men

quote: I wonder how many people I've looked at all my life and never seen.
author: John Steinbeck,  The Winter of Our Discontent

quote: Shut your eyes and see.
author: James Joyce

quote: You may choose to look the other way but you can never say again that you did not know.
author: William Wilberforce

quote: You don't look out there for God, something in the sky, you look in you.
author: Alan Watts

quote: I see your picture and in that picture I didn't see you.
author: Santosh Kalwar,  Obscurity

quote: Maybe sometimes we can only see the truth about ourselves if someone shows us where to look.
author: Michelle Hodkin,  The Retribution of Mara Dyer

quote: You know that look that women get when they want to have sex? Me neither.
author: Steve Martin

quote: I always look like I’m lying. I was born with a politician’s face. You’ll know I’m in love when I have a Vote For Me look in my eyes.
author: Jarod Kintz,  This Book is Not FOR SALE

quote: Don't think, but look! (PI 66)
author: Ludwig Wittgenstein

quote: O Lord, you have searched me and you know me.
author: Anonymous,  Holy Bible: King James Version

quote: I'm pretty much looking for beauty all the time. It just seems like some days the light is better to see it.
author: Melodie Ramone

quote: I shut my eyes in order to see.
author: Paul Gauguin

quote: It's the mind that sees, not eyes.
author: Toba Beta,  Master of Stupidity

quote: I don't mind making jokes, but I don't want to look like one.
author: Marilyn Monroe

quote: Honest is how I want to look. The truth doesn't glitter and shine.
author: Chuck Palahniuk,  Survivor

quote: Think, think, think.
author: A.A. Milne,  Winnie-the-Pooh

quote: So many things become beautiful when you really look.
author: Lauren Oliver,  Before I Fall

quote: If I never meet you In this lifeLet me feel the lackA glance from your eyesThen my life Will be yours
author: James Jones,  The Thin Red Line

quote: ...you look at me like an emergency
author: Adrienne Rich,  Diving Into the Wreck

quote: To look life in the face, always, to look life in the face, and to know it for what it is...at last, to love it for what it is, and then, to put it away...
author: Virginia Woolf

quote: I look for you in every life, but I don't always find you. And sometimes I find you too late.
author: Kirsten Miller,  The Eternal Ones

quote: See, don't just look. Your partner is so much more than their appearance. It's how kind their heart is, how lovely they smile, how much they care and have compassion, how generous and giving they are which becomes much more attractive.
author: Suzan Battah,  Five Senses of Romance A Self Help Guide for Gentlemen and Ladies, Both Single and Taken

quote: when you're not looking, somebody'll sneak up and write "Fuck you"right under your nose.
author: J.D. Salinger,  The Catcher in the Rye

quote: Everything has beauty, but not everyone sees it.
author: Confucius

quote: What you see is what you see
author: Frank Stella

quote: Look for God, suggests my Guru. Look for God like a man with his head on fire looks for water.
author: Elizabeth Gilbert

quote: To gaze into another persons face is to do two things: to recognise their humanity and to assert your own.
author: Lawrence Hill,  Someone Knows My Name

quote: I look at you, and I think about you, and ... I don't know. No one has ever confounded me the way you do.
author: Stephanie Perkins,  Lola and the Boy Next Door

quote: I may not look like much, but I'm an expert at pretending to be a ninja.
author: Darynda Jones,  First Grave on the Right

quote: Sometimes people are beautiful.Not in looks.Not in what they say.Just in what they are.
author: Markus Zusak,  I Am the Messenger

quote: I hate when women give me that look. That overlook.
author: Jarod Kintz,  A Story That Talks about Talking Is Like Chatter to Chattering Teeth, and Every Set of Dentures Can Attest to the Fact That No..

quote: Look. Survey. Inspect. My hair is ruined! I look like a pan of bacon and eggs!
author: Diana Wynne Jones,  Howl's Moving Castle

quote: I look in the mirror through the eyes of the child that was me.
author: Judy Collins

quote: I think that it's hard for vain people to be funny. I think you can look any way you want as long as you have a good sense of humor about yourself. People who are concerned with their looks and what they're wearing and how they present themselves tend to have less of a sense of humor about themselves.
author: Taran Killam

quote: If you seek happiness, look in the mirror. If you seek love, look elsewhere.
author: Thomas F. Shubnell

quote: To enlighten your life, see beauty.
author: Debasish Mridha

quote: You look up when you wish to be exalted. And I look down because I am exalted.
author: Friedrich Nietzsche,  Thus Spoke Zarathustra

quote: Have you noticed how nobody ever looks up? Nobody looks at chimneys, or trees against the sky, or the tops of buildings. Everybody just looks down at the pavement or their shoes. The whole world could pass them by and most people wouldn't notice.
author: Julie Andrews Edwards,  The Last of the Really Great Whangdoodles
